      "date": "2016-05-11 08:57:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\n(1 comment)\n\nIt is preferred that sub-commands for lfs and lctl get their own man page, like \"lfs-mdts.1\" in this case.  \n\nHowever, it isn't clear there would be a benefit in this case since there aren't any options to this command, nor a lot of description needed to explain what it does, so I think it is OK in this case.\n\nJust thought I would mention this in case other lfs/lctl sub-commands need new/modified man pages.",
